                  <unitid type="work">poems.pare</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">[Parody on an Epitaph]</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">Now clean, now hideous, mellow now, now gruff,</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1882" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1882</unitdate>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  82</bibref>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  256-257</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Composed shortly after visiting the church at <geogname normal="Appleby        (Cumbria, England, United Kingdom), inhabited place        [7010157]">Appleby</geogname>, <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1767"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17670903"
                              certainty="circa"
                              era="ce"
                              calendar="gregorian">c. 3 September 1767</date>
                     </extref>,
							while on a short tour of the Lake District with <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Wharton, Thomas, 1717-1794"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname role="trc" normal="Wharton, Thomas, 1717-1794">Thomas
								Wharton</persname>
                     </extref>.
							First published, untitled, in <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#GoE_1889"
                             linktype="simple"> Gosse,
								<title render="italic" linktype="simple">Gray</title> (1882),  176</bibref>.
						</p>
               </scopecontent>
